airbnbApart.title: Introducing Airbnb-friendly apartments
airbnbApart.apartAirbnb: We've partnered with apartment building across the US that let you rent place to live and airbnb it part-time. Explore available apartments and find out what you can earn

reply.question: Is my place right for Airbnb?
reply.reply: Airbnb guests are interested in all kinds of places. We have listings for tiny homes, cabins, threeHouses, and more. Even a spaces room can be great places for stays

reply.question: Do I have to host all time?
reply.reply: Not at all—you control your calendar. You can host once a year, a few nights, month or even often

reply.question: How much shoud I interact with guest?
reply.reply: It's up to you. Some host prefes to message guest only at the key moments—like sending a short note when they check in—while others also enjoy meeting their guest in person. You'll find a style that works for you and you guests.

reply.question: Any tips for being greate Aibnb host?
reply.reply: Getting the basic down goes long way. Keep you place clean, respond to guest promptly, and provide necessary amenities, like fresh towel. Some Host like add personal touch, such as putting out fresh flowers or sharing a list of local place to explore—but it's not required

reply.question: What are Airbnb fees?
reply.reply: Airbnb typically collects a flast service fee of 3% of the reservation subtotal when you get paid. We also collect a fee from guests when they book. In many arears, Airbnb collects and pays sales and tourism taxe automatically on your behalf as well.
